{
  "texts": [
    "This analysis unveils several persistent and potential ethical and societal consequences.",
    "First, the lack of scientific validity of the ETA itself contributes to the lack of quality in the information based on which people make decisions regarding AI systems.",
    "Misguiding existential presupposition can lead to poor decisions on the part of policymakers when it comes to regulation and other safeguards, potentially leading to ignoring use cases that could actually cause existential risks: which systems should we automate, and which not?",
    "How do we make sure we do not overly trust the existing AI systems (automation bias; see, e,g.",
    "[81]) as safety components of critical systems?"
  ]
}